			  			Well before I see complaints posted here of me fluffing up a large number of fleets to take council planets and raise my score I decided to post this and probably pay for it as becoming a target. Yes, I do have 100 fleets right now. Yes, that does look like I'm fleet fluffing to do a mass planet grab. No, I can't take that many planets because about 60-70 of those fleets are a 1 gunboat fleet called Reserve-Training which can't take planets since only cruisers+ can take planets. I was bored at work and decided to test something so I spent a turn cranking out roughly 1 gunboat per commander I had sitting without a fleet. I spent about 3 hours going 1 at a time assigning each commander a single gun boat then I sent them all out to train. Why you may ask, because I would rather spend a lot of time now getting some good commanders so that when I can afford to crank out 100 cruisers or bigger in a few turns I have some commander with experience under their belt. Believe me, this costs a chunk of change for ship upkeep but I am hoping that the overall training of the commanders will pay off in end game. Attack if you feel that I am wrong in trying to train those lazy commanders that sit around doing nothing all day while my other hard working commanders strive to protect my empire but I feel this is worth the time to invest, will let you know if it turns out to be worth it if you all want to know.<br />
